{
  "stem": "16345.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Most of them-- most of them seemed to go about it as if it was their life's work.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By this time, it started getting to be every man for himself.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there's another thing I think I should mention.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like, for instance, by that time, we knew that our grandparents, that the older people, the people who didn't-- not wind up in camps, wound up in places like Treblinka, which were death camps.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there were-- they had all been gassed and killed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The rumor mill.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody-- nobody gave us videos or pictures.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We knew some of them, like Majdanek, Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were-- there were rumors going around.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, a lot of people didn't want to believe it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, oh, how-- how could you believe in atrocities like this and senseless barbarism or senseless killing of older people and children and just killing of everybody?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were-- we were civilized people, and we assumed that most other people were civilized also.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in spite of the fact that the Polish people didn't treat us like friends-- occasionally, they had a pogrom and beat up and possibly killed some people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we're talking about wholesale slaughter, where my grandparents were sent.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father and I both sat there and cried through the night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I remember one of the-- one of the-- one of the-- my Polish co-workers said, hey, Henjek, I hear your mother was barbecued, things like that.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They told us we are leaving.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, they told us we're leaving because they were going to take us to Germany to another work camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The rumor mills were always strong, and they were telling us-- the rumor mills were telling us, nothing was officially announced-- we're going to Germany.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
